<figure id="CNX_UPhysics_35_05_CorneaLens">
<media id="fs-id1167134644639" alt="Figure shows a tree in front of an eye. Rays from the top and bottom of the tree strike the cornea of the eye. They are refracted, intersect in the middle of the vitreous humor and reach the retina. The image formed on the retina is tiny and inverted.">
